definitions.definition: ( originally ) Any unit of (originally cultural ) information , such as a practice or idea , that is transmitted verbally or by repeated action from one mind to another in a comparable way to the transmission of genes .
( Internet ) Media , usually humorous, which is copied and circulated online with slight adaptations, such as basic pictures , video templates, etc. [from 1993]
examples: He posted a meme that went viral within a few hours on social media.
He stuck memes on the wall to campaign for the position of President.

definitions.definition: ( Internet ) A specific instance of a meme, such as an image macro or a video , often with humorous superimposed text.
examples: This meme generator lets you make your own memes by adding a caption to existing images, or by uploading your own image.
I'm always posting memes on the groupchat.

definitions.definition: ( Internet slang , derogatory ) Something which is deceptive ; a trick , a ruse .
examples: It's a meme degree, you know. Good luck getting a job from that.
I can't believe I fell for the bulking meme .

definitions.definition: ( Internet slang , derogatory ) Something not to be taken seriously ; a joke .
examples: It's a meme degree, you know. Good luck getting a job from that.

definitions.definition: ( Internet ) A work produced and shared in response to a prompt or suggestion within an online group.
